title: For Sale:  Inteliscope
postcontent: You might think strapping your smartphone to a firearm is the last thing you'd want to do with it, but what if it could provide helpful information while hunting or during target practice? That's just what inventor Jason Giddings and his new company, Inteliscope, LLC, decided to do when they combined guns with smart devices to launch the Inteliscope Tactical Rifle Adapter. Along with an iOS app, the adapter allows gun owners to mount their iPhone or iPod Touch to a firearm and use it as a sight with a heads-up display showing real-time data on their surroundings. The Inteliscope adapter provides a protective cover for an iPhone or iPod Touch that can quickly attach and release from a Picatinny (Mil-STD-1913) or Weaver tactical rail. Using an app, the iOS device can then act as a gun sight, complete with 5x digital zoom and an adjustable mount that lets users peek around corners. The app also works in portrait mode, so the adapter can be affixed to the side of a firearm if needed. It's hard to imagine an iPhone giving a clearer view than a standard scope, but the included app does offer some features to turn it into a handy heads-up display. Aside from a choice of different cross hairs, users will be able to see data on local prevailing winds, GPS coordinates, a compass, ballistics info, and a shot timer, all at a glance. The attached device can even act as a mounted flashlight or strobe, but probably the most useful feature is the ability to record and play back video of each shot.

title: For Sale:  .50AE Desert Eagle Titanium Gold Tiger Striped
postcontent:
The Magnum Research Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic large-frame pistol chambered in .50 AE. Desert Eagles don’t have a typical pistol design instead it uses a gas-operated rotating bolt, which is a trait more common for rifles. It has a fixed barrel and front end, so the bolt blows back instead of a slide. Features include an ambidextrous safety and when engaged it disables the trigger and blocks the firing pin, so even if it drops it won’t discharge. Magnum Research's founders, Jim Skildum and John Risdall had been involved with the company since 1979. Both men oversaw the ascent of the Desert Eagle® Pistol from a concept on paper to a pop culture icon including a Playboy magazine front cover featuring Pamela Anderson showing off a Pink Desert Eagle pistol. Since 2009 the Desert Eagle Pistol has been produced in the USA at MRI's Pillager, MN facility. The Desert Eagle pistols are made in a number of distinctive and appealing finishes including classic brushed chrome and the latest the distinctive and collectable  “Tiger Stripe” pattern - a Gold Titanium Nitride Authentic Bengal Tiger Striped coated finish, which is a very hard surface.

This gun includes an extra MR magazine [7 rounds] and 200 boxes [20 rds ea.] - 400 total rounds of factory 300 -325 Gr. ammo. This gun and the ammo are very hard to find on the open market, NIB [New in the box] as these are. I have four as described herein for $15K.

Must have South Carolina CWP or an FFL. Sale must be for pickup near me location with signed and witnessed copies of my bill of sale. You must be a qualified buyer under South Carolina State Law.

p.s. If you can find it cheaper - go buy it!

Desert Eagle Technical Data
General Features

The Picatinny rail located on the barrel runs from the chamber area to right behind the front sight allowing the use of scope rings (optional) and aftermarket optics.

    The Desert Eagle Pistol is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol with a rotating three lug bolt for positive lock-up.
    The barrel is locked in place, assuring a high degree of accuracy.
    The polygonal rifling reduces barrel wear, is easy to clean and very accurate.
    Anatomically formed grip, ideal hand seating angle and comfortable grip dimensions permit rapid, accurate, instinctive shooting. The Desert Eagle is designed for two-handed shooting.
    The Desert Eagle Pistol fires standard factory ammunition.
    The Desert Eagle Pistol has an automatic slide lock that holds the slide open after the last round is fired.

On The Border Free Entree

title: For Sale:  .50AE Desert Eagle Titanium Gold Tiger Striped
postcontent:
The Magnum Research Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic large-frame pistol chambered in .50 AE. Desert Eagles don’t have a typical pistol design instead it uses a gas-operated rotating bolt, which is a trait more common for rifles. It has a fixed barrel and front end, so the bolt blows back instead of a slide. Features include an ambidextrous safety and when engaged it disables the trigger and blocks the firing pin, so even if it drops it won’t discharge. Magnum Research's founders, Jim Skildum and John Risdall had been involved with the company since 1979. Both men oversaw the ascent of the Desert Eagle® Pistol from a concept on paper to a pop culture icon including a Playboy magazine front cover featuring Pamela Anderson showing off a Pink Desert Eagle pistol. Since 2009 the Desert Eagle Pistol has been produced in the USA at MRI's Pillager, MN facility. The Desert Eagle pistols are made in a number of distinctive and appealing finishes including classic brushed chrome and the latest the distinctive and collectable “Tiger Stripe” pattern - a Gold Titanium Nitride Authentic Bengal Tiger Striped coated finish, which is a very hard surface.

This gun includes an extra MR magazine [7 rounds] and 20 boxes [20 rds ea.] - 400 total rounds of factory 300 -325 Gr. ammo. This gun and the ammo are very hard to find on the open market, NIB [New in the box] as these are. I have four as described herein for $15K.

Must have South Carolina CWP or an FFL. Sale must be for pickup near me location with signed and witnessed copies of my bill of sale. You must be a qualified buyer under South Carolina State Law.

p.s. If you can find it cheaper - go buy it!

Desert Eagle Technical Data
General Features

The Picatinny rail located on the barrel runs from the chamber area to right behind the front sight allowing the use of scope rings (optional) and aftermarket optics.

The Desert Eagle Pistol is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol with a rotating three lug bolt for positive lock-up.
The barrel is locked in place, assuring a high degree of accuracy.
The polygonal rifling reduces barrel wear, is easy to clean and very accurate.
Anatomically formed grip, ideal hand seating angle and comfortable grip dimensions permit rapid, accurate, instinctive shooting. The Desert Eagle is designed for two-handed shooting.
The Desert Eagle Pistol fires standard factory ammunition.
The Desert Eagle Pistol has an automatic slide lock that holds the slide open after the last round is fired.

postcontent:
The Magnum Research Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic large-frame pistol chambered in .50 AE. Desert Eagles don’t have a typical pistol design instead it uses a gas-operated rotating bolt, which is a trait more common for rifles. It has a fixed barrel and front end, so the bolt blows back instead of a slide. Features include an ambidextrous safety and when engaged it disables the trigger and blocks the firing pin, so even if it drops it won’t discharge. Magnum Research's founders, Jim Skildum and John Risdall had been involved with the company since 1979. Both men oversaw the ascent of the Desert Eagle® Pistol from a concept on paper to a pop culture icon including a Playboy magazine front cover featuring Pamela Anderson showing off a Pink Desert Eagle pistol. Since 2009 the Desert Eagle Pistol has been produced in the USA at MRI's Pillager, MN facility. The Desert Eagle pistols are made in a number of distinctive and appealing finishes including classic brushed chrome and the latest the distinctive and collectable “Tiger Stripe” pattern - a Gold Titanium Nitride - Authentic Bengal Tiger Striped coated finish, which is a very hard surface. The DE is very easy to disassemble for cleaning. Warranty papers are in each box, including safety cable and Bolt tool.

This [each] gun includes an extra MR magazine [7 rounds] and 20 boxes [20 rds ea.] - 400 total rounds of factory 300 -325 Gr. ammo. p.s. If you can find it cheaper somewhere else - be my guest, go buy it!

Desert Eagle Technical Data
General Features

The Picatinny rail located on the barrel runs from the chamber area to right behind the front sight allowing the use of scope rings (optional) and aftermarket optics.

The Desert Eagle Pistol is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol with a rotating three lug bolt for positive lock-up.
The barrel is locked in place, assuring a high degree of accuracy.
The polygonal rifling reduces barrel wear, is easy to clean and very accurate.
Anatomically formed grip, ideal hand seating angle and comfortable grip dimensions permit rapid, accurate, instinctive shooting. The Desert Eagle is designed for two-handed shooting.
The Desert Eagle Pistol fires standard factory ammunition.

postcontent:
This P11 Hard Chrome has had the feed ramp and barrel polished. It also has a polished trigger shoe up grade and a Hogue grip sleeve.  Additionally, it comes with 2 factory Megar 10 round magazines, 2 trigger locks and a hard storage case. This gun runs smoothly with out jamming or any other malfunction. 
Manufactures description:
   The P-11 uses an aluminum receiver inside a polymer grip housing held on with polymer pins. The slide, barrel, and magazine are steel. The standard magazine holds ten rounds, or twelve rounds in states not limited to 10 round magazines. Both fit flush to the bottom of the pistol. At 14 oz (400 g) unloaded, the handgun itself is comparatively light. The P-11 lacks an external manual safety relying instead on a long and heavy double action only (DAO) trigger pull, which requires nine pounds of pressure, to prevent accidental discharge. A firing pin spring and low-mass hammer prevent discharge if the gun is dropped. The P-11 will also accept some Smith and Wesson 59 series magazines.[2] An available adapter wraps around the base of 15-round Smith & Wesson model 59 style magazines. Smith & Wesson series 69 compact 12 round magazines will also work, with a matching short adapter sleeve as well. Accessories such as trigger shoes, finger-rests, belt clips, steel guide rods to replace the factory installed polymer guide rod, gray and OD green colored polymer grip housings, night sights and other accessories are also available from the manufacturer.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Trapper 44 Magnum
postcontent:
Nice Winchester Trapper 44 Magnum. Excellent gun for hunting whitetails, hogs or inexpensive centerfire plinking. This gun has a 16 inch barrel and is very light and compact. It would make a great home defense, youth or ladies gun. 

The good: it is a Winchester, has the best trigger pull I have ever found on a factory lever action, slick operating action, good clean bore, reasonably accurate - shoots 3 1/2 inch groups at 80 yards with cheap ammunition and iron sights, fast handling, a joy to carry, and the stock is in very good condition with just a few minor scratches. It is absolutely fun to shoot!

The bad and ugly: This is a hunter/shooter grade firearm. While everything works perfect, this gun was not babied by its former owner. There are scratches, wear marks and some previous rust freckles on the receiver and barrel that are not a big deal for a utility field gun but in the real world make it less desirable for collectors and folks looking for perfection.  I did my best to take photos that fairly represent the cosmetic defects.

Give this gun a good home and put some venison on your table. Despite its cosmetic imperfections, it still is a handsome Winchester that will not lose value. I am a private seller and can ship to a FFL for $30. If you need FFL to FFL add another $30. I appreciate you looking. I will accept US Postal Money Order for immediate shipping or will ship after your personal check clears.
